  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering through various mechanisms and frameworks:\n\n1. Global Standards\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Establishing common anti-money laundering (AML) principles\n- Setting international compliance standards\n\n2. Treaty Frameworks\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Palermo Convention\n- Vienna Convention\n- Multilateral agreements on financial transparency\n\n3. Regulatory Coordination\n- Information sharing between national financial intelligence units\n- Cross-border investigation protocols\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\n4. Implementation Mechanisms\n- Requiring countries to criminalize money laundering\n- Mandating suspicious transaction reporting\n- Establishing beneficial ownership transparency\n\n5. Enforcement Collaboration\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint international investigations\n- Coordinated asset seizure and recovery procedures\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Due diligence standards\n- Risk-based monitoring approaches\n\n7. Technological Integration\n- Shared digital platforms for tracking financial transactions\n- International data exchange networks\n- Blockchain and cryptocurrency tracking mechanisms\n\nThese intersections create a comprehensive global approach to combating financial crimes and money laundering.",
